{"change_summary":"Normalized legacy milestone task-run history in the filesystem adapter by collapsing old start/completion row pairs for bead queries, ignoring superseded legacy start rows during completion updates, and including `run_id` in duplicate-finalization errors. Added regression coverage for legacy query collapse and no-`run_id` retry finalization, and documented that `task-runs.ndjson` remains the repair source of truth because snapshot and journal writes are still non-transactional follow-ups.","outstanding_risks":["Task-run finalization still updates lineage, snapshot, and journal files separately; an interrupted write can leave snapshot or journal state behind the lineage file until a repair or reconciliation pass rebuilds from `task-runs.ndjson`."],"steps":[{"description":"Patched `FsTaskRunLineageStore` to detect legacy paired attempts by bead, project, and `started_at`, collapse them in `find_runs_for_bead`, exclude superseded legacy running rows from update disambiguation, and include `run_id` in already-finalized errors.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Documented the non-transactional lineage, snapshot, and journal update order in the milestone service so interrupted completions clearly point operators at `task-runs.ndjson` as the durable repair source.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Added milestone_record regression tests covering legacy paired-row query collapse, legacy no-`run_id` retry finalization, and the improved duplicate-finalization diagnostic.","order":2,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Ran formatting, milestone_record unit tests, and clippy validation after the changes.","order":3,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 67 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}